SIMPLE: threap
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Threap
<hw>Threap</hw> <pr>(thr⟦emac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Threaped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Threaping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧re⟦aacute⟧pian</ets> to reprove.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>threpe</asp>, and <asp>threip</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
call; to name.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To maintain obstinately against denial or
contradiction; also, to contend or argue against (another) with
obstinacy; to chide; <as>as, he <ex>threaped</ex> me down that it was
so</as>.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To beat, or thrash.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To cozen, or cheat.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Threap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Threap
<hw>Threap</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To contend obstinately; to be
pertinacious.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It's not for a man with a woman to <qex>threap</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Percy's Reliques.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Threap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Threap
<hw>Threap</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An obstinate decision
or determination; a pertinacious affirmation.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was taken a <qex>threap</qex> that he would have it finished
before the year was done.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Threat</ent>⟦br⟧
